# Teldat  Add-on for Splunk

## System requirements
- Teldat CIT Router
- Splunk 9.0 or newer

## Installation
1. Open Splunk GUI
2. Navigate to "Apps" (upper right corner) > "Find more apps" 
3. Search for "Teldat"
4. Click install.

## Configuration
### Splunk
- Configure a new index for the new logs (Settings > New Index)

#### Receiving syslogs on Splunk
- Configure new UDP port (Settings > Data inputs > UDP (Add new)) (e.g. 514) pointing to the new index using the "syslog:teldat" sourcetype

### Teldat
1. Configure syslog events to be sent.
2. Configure IP and Port for event to be sent to.
